00:38.038 --> 00:39.938
## [Jazzy Solo ]

01:00.026 --> 01:01.926
[ Beeping ]

01:02.028 --> 01:03.928
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.298 --> 01:07.232
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:11.604 --> 01:12.935
Whoo-hoo!

01:22.549 --> 01:26.007
## [ Singing ]

01:30.190 --> 01:32.818
- Homer!
- ## [ Singing ]

01:32.926 --> 01:36.521
- I said, Homer!
- ## [ Ends ]

01:36.629 --> 01:38.563
Marge, I'm out of beer!

01:38.665 --> 01:44.604
You know, Homie, a lot of men use their Saturdays
to do things around the house. Hint, hint.

01:44.704 --> 01:47.468
But, Marge, I'm not like other men.

01:47.574 --> 01:50.907
That's why you buy my pants
at that special store!

01:51.010 --> 01:55.310
I'm serious! You never finished
painting the garage.

01:55.415 --> 02:00.045
And you still haven't taken down those awful
hostage ribbons from the old oak tree.

02:00.153 --> 02:03.680
Oh, you know as soon as I take 'em down,
there'll just be more hostages.

02:03.790 --> 02:06.987
And you could at least get
that snake out of the piano.

02:07.093 --> 02:09.960
<i>- ## [ Middle Eastern ]
- [ Hissing ]</i>

02:10.062 --> 02:13.294
Fine, I'll drop everything
I'm doing just for you!

02:13.399 --> 02:16.857
[ Slurps ] But you'll have to live
with the guilt of ruining my Saturday.

02:16.970 --> 02:19.666
Can you live with that, Marge?
Huh? Can ya?

02:19.772 --> 02:21.672
- Yup!
- Can ya?

02:22.408 --> 02:24.205
<i>- [ Groans ]
- [ Thuds ]</i>

02:24.310 --> 02:26.210
<i>[ Ned ]
God... bless him.!</i>

02:29.282 --> 02:31.716
<i>[ Doorbell Chimes ]</i>

02:31.818 --> 02:34.719
- Excuse me. I have a few questions for Pop.
- That's me.

02:34.821 --> 02:38.689
You're Pop? No offense,
but even I could kick your ass.

02:38.791 --> 02:41.351
Hey, get off my case! The only
reason I'm working here...

02:41.461 --> 02:43.725
is 'cause I'm trying
to get a date with Mom.

02:46.466 --> 02:49.458
Look, Pop. I'm planning some
expert home repairs...

02:49.569 --> 02:52.265
and I need a pair of
bolt cutters or wire cutters...

02:52.372 --> 02:54.772
or something to get
the lock off my toolbox.

02:54.874 --> 02:56.933
Aisle one, next to the cat poison.

02:59.245 --> 03:04.182
Edna, look. A dimmer switch could
ratchet up the romance in our love nest.

03:04.284 --> 03:06.775
You mean the janitor's closet?
Ha!

03:06.886 --> 03:08.945
[ Sighs ]
What's the matter, Edna?

03:09.055 --> 03:11.683
Lately you just say, ''Ha!''
to everything.

03:11.791 --> 03:13.782
<i>I want a baby now.!</i>

03:15.695 --> 03:19.096
Why don't we continue this
in Pool Supplies?

03:19.199 --> 03:21.724
Hi, I'm Doug Vaccaro.

03:21.834 --> 03:26.635
<i>You know me as Chip, the wisecracking assistant
on the hit sitcom Toolin'Around.</i>

03:26.739 --> 03:29.606
[ Titters ]
A man in an apron! [ Chuckles ]

03:29.709 --> 03:33.440
But today I'm here as a ''tool''
of Global Dynamics Corp.

03:33.546 --> 03:35.776
You know, installing
your own barbecue pit...

03:35.882 --> 03:39.579
is no harder than adding an aviary
or Olympic-size swimming pool.

03:39.686 --> 03:42.621
- In fact, it's a snap.
- [ Fingers Snap ]

03:42.722 --> 03:45.885
- Or if you're not into chicken-
- No, no! I'm into chicken!

03:45.992 --> 03:49.155
How about wild boar?
Or swordfish?

03:49.262 --> 03:51.787
Or hippo?

03:51.898 --> 03:54.093
Mmm. Hippo.

03:54.200 --> 03:56.100
[ Guttural Sigh ]

03:56.202 --> 03:58.170
[ Male Announcer]
Lighthearted apron not included.

03:58.271 --> 04:01.035
Snapping fingers
may not make food appear.

04:01.140 --> 04:04.439
How about it, Bart?
Would you like a new backyard barbecue pit?

04:04.544 --> 04:06.512
Can I burn evidence in it?

04:06.613 --> 04:09.241
<i>We can all burn evidence in it.</i>

04:11.985 --> 04:15.045
There. That wasn't so hard,
was it, honey?

04:15.154 --> 04:18.317
Dad, I really need to rest my back.

04:18.423 --> 04:21.291
Okay, sweetie.
Daddy'll take over.

04:22.462 --> 04:26.091
Oh, yeah.
That's a fine-looking-

04:26.199 --> 04:28.667
D'oh! Okay, no big deal.

04:28.768 --> 04:31.066
[ Straining ]

04:31.170 --> 04:34.537
[ Shrieks ]
Stupid Lisa! [ Panting ]

04:34.641 --> 04:37.576
Gotta build fast. Cement drying!
All right, let's see.

04:37.677 --> 04:42.307
Ohh. English side ruined!
Must use French instructions!

04:42.415 --> 04:45.714
<i>''Le grille''?
What the hell is that?</i>

04:45.818 --> 04:48.719
[ Groans ]
Come here. Get- Uh.

04:48.821 --> 04:51.551
Come on. Fit, you-
[ Muttering ]

04:52.592 --> 04:54.753
Huh?
[ Groaning ]

04:54.861 --> 04:57.625
<i>Ahh.! Yeah.!</i>

04:57.730 --> 05:00.824
<i>That's one
fine-looking barbecue pit.</i>

05:00.933 --> 05:04.460
Why doesn't mine look like that?
[ Screams ]

05:04.570 --> 05:06.538
Why? Da-Why?

05:06.639 --> 05:09.335
Why must life be so hard?

05:09.442 --> 05:14.675
Why must I fail in every attempt at masonry?
[ Crying ]

05:14.781 --> 05:16.976
How's your father's project
coming along?

05:17.083 --> 05:19.051
I think he's almost done.

05:19.152 --> 05:22.121
- [ Screams ]
- Yeah, he's done.

05:23.423 --> 05:25.584
<i>[ Doorbell Chimes ]</i>

05:25.692 --> 05:28.593
[ Clears Throat ]
I'd like to return this barbecue kit.

05:28.695 --> 05:32.131
All returned items must be in a box
and accompanied by a receipt.

05:32.231 --> 05:34.199
Well, if you'll
follow the flashlight...

05:34.300 --> 05:37.326
you'll see the receipt
embedded here and here...

05:37.437 --> 05:40.235
and elements of the box here,
here and possibly here.

05:40.340 --> 05:42.467
Sorry. I didn't get
this hammer hat...

05:42.575 --> 05:45.669
- by handing out refunds.
- [ Groans ]

05:45.778 --> 05:48.906
[ Grunting ]
Come on! Get- Ohh!

05:49.015 --> 05:53.111
Yeah, hold on there, Santa Claus.
That box is for toys only.

05:53.219 --> 05:58.714
Well, of course. Any kid would love
to have this, uh, activity center.

05:58.825 --> 06:03.091
- It teaches them while they learn.
- Yeah. Nice try, St. Nick.

06:03.196 --> 06:05.289
Now hit the road, Kriss Kringle.

06:05.398 --> 06:09.095
- But- But-
- You heard me, Pere Noel.

06:11.738 --> 06:13.638
[ Groans ]

06:14.674 --> 06:17.074
- What you got there?
- Beanie Baby.

06:20.947 --> 06:22.915
[ Squeaking ]

06:25.952 --> 06:27.920
I'll never get rid of it.

06:28.020 --> 06:30.488
<i>- It'll follow me to the ends of the earth!
- [ Thudding ]</i>

06:32.225 --> 06:34.420
All right!
My bumper fell off.

06:35.595 --> 06:37.790
[ Horns Honking ]

06:37.897 --> 06:41.264
Not my fault. Act of God, act of God.
[ Chuckles ]

06:41.367 --> 06:45.235
[ Horn Blares, Dies ]

06:45.338 --> 06:47.499
Uh-oh. Uh-

06:47.607 --> 06:48.904
Ahh!

06:53.746 --> 06:56.306
## [ Singing ]

06:58.584 --> 07:00.552
Homie, someone's at the door.

07:00.653 --> 07:04.020
They want to talk to you about
some sort of car accident?

07:04.123 --> 07:06.250
Take the kids out back.

07:06.359 --> 07:08.327
I'll handle this.

07:09.629 --> 07:11.529
Mr. Simpson?

07:12.799 --> 07:15.927
I believe something of yours
struck my car yesterday.

07:16.035 --> 07:18.663
Oh, yeah? Prove it!

07:18.771 --> 07:20.898
That's your license plate, isn't it?

07:22.308 --> 07:25.436
Uh-
[ Crying ]

07:25.545 --> 07:28.036
All right!
Just go ahead and sue me!

07:28.147 --> 07:32.948
Everybody else does!
The average settlement is $68,000.

07:33.052 --> 07:36.954
I'm not here to sue you.
My name is Astrid Weller.

07:37.056 --> 07:40.856
I own an art gallery,
and I'd love to display your piece.

07:40.960 --> 07:43.827
You mean this hunk of junk?
This isn't art.

07:43.930 --> 07:46.296
It's just a barbecue
that pushed me over the edge.

07:46.399 --> 07:50.426
Didn't you? Didn't you? You stupid-
[ Shouting ]

07:50.536 --> 07:52.766
Uh, art isn't just pretty pictures.

07:52.872 --> 07:57.104
It's an expression of raw human emotion.
In your case, rage.

07:57.210 --> 07:59.178
Oh, I got that, lady.

07:59.278 --> 08:03.146
Is everything okay?
I got worried when I didn't hear any shots.

08:03.249 --> 08:06.980
- This lady says I'm an artist.
- You? An artist?

08:07.086 --> 08:11.113
Your husband's work
is what we call ''outsider art.''

08:11.224 --> 08:16.184
- It could be by a mental patient
or a hillbilly or a chimpanzee.
- [ Gasps ]

08:16.295 --> 08:21.096
<i>In high school I was voted most likely to be
a mental patient, hillbilly or chimpanzee!</i>

08:21.200 --> 08:23.862
Well, you should be very excited...

08:23.970 --> 08:27.098
because outsider art
couldn't be hotter.

08:27.206 --> 08:30.937
So you'd better catch the fever.
Catch it!

08:33.513 --> 08:35.481
[ Chattering ]

08:38.251 --> 08:40.150
[ Munching ]

08:40.253 --> 08:44.485
Dad, chew with your mouth closed.
You're losing your mystique.

08:44.590 --> 08:47.115
Lisa, all great artists
love free food.

08:47.226 --> 08:49.854
Check outJasperJohns.

08:49.962 --> 08:52.897
You squeal on me, I'll kill you.

08:52.999 --> 08:55.866
[ Groans ]
I don't know.

08:55.968 --> 08:59.529
I studied art for years,
but I just don't get this.

08:59.639 --> 09:02.164
Sounds like somebody's jealous.

09:02.275 --> 09:07.645
No, I'm not. I just can't believe some people
are paying hundreds of dollars...

09:07.747 --> 09:10.511
for something a hillbilly
pulled out of the trash.

09:10.616 --> 09:16.179
Hey, I done studied for years
on how to get over that junkyard fence.

09:16.289 --> 09:19.190
Then I learnt the gate was open.

09:19.292 --> 09:22.386
Smithers, I think I'm in love!

09:22.495 --> 09:24.986
- Hah!
- With this sculpture.

09:25.097 --> 09:29.431
Sir, that's by Homer Simpson.
I don't think you want to buy it.

09:29.535 --> 09:35.201
<i>Smithers, years ago I blew the chance to buy
Picasso's Guernica for a song.</i>

09:35.308 --> 09:37.276
Luckily that song was
''White Christmas''...

09:37.376 --> 09:39.367
and by hanging on to it,
I made billions.

09:39.478 --> 09:42.447
Anyway, I love this hideous thing.

09:42.548 --> 09:44.709
Young lady, I'll take it!

09:44.817 --> 09:46.808
Congratulations, Homer.

09:46.919 --> 09:50.184
- You're now a professional artist.
- Whoo-hoo!

09:50.289 --> 09:52.621
Look, Marge!
My first sale!

09:52.725 --> 09:55.956
- In your face,JasperJohns!
- Huh?

09:58.898 --> 10:00.991
<i>[ Homer Grunting ]</i>

10:04.003 --> 10:05.630
Where you going with that junk, Dad?

10:05.738 --> 10:07.501
I'm gonna be an outsider artist.

10:07.607 --> 10:10.667
That way I can turn all these old baseball cards,
Disney memorabilia...

10:10.776 --> 10:13.074
and antiques
into something valuable.

10:13.179 --> 10:18.617
Homie, I'm really happy you sold your sculpture.
But don't you think it may have been a fluke?

10:18.718 --> 10:22.620
Hey, I've always had an interest in art,
dating back to my schoolgirl days...

10:22.722 --> 10:26.021
when I painted portrait
after portrait of Ringo Starr.

10:26.125 --> 10:28.218
That's my life you're describing!

10:28.327 --> 10:31.956
I think I remember
my own life, Marge.

10:32.064 --> 10:36.694
Astrid said the key to my art is anger.
But you know me. I'm Mr. Mellow.

10:36.802 --> 10:40.636
- [ Together] Hmm?
- So I'm giving you kids permission to get me mad.

10:40.740 --> 10:43.709
- Come on. Give me what you got.
- Well, if it'll help.

10:43.809 --> 10:47.540
Uh, Mom found out her engagement ring
is made of rock candy.

10:47.647 --> 10:51.515
[ Grunting ]
Good work, honey. Keep it coming.

10:51.617 --> 10:54.745
Well, I'm flunking math, and the other day
I was a little attracted to Milhouse.

10:54.854 --> 10:57.652
[ Shouting, Screaming ]

11:02.128 --> 11:04.028
Moe, this is Astrid, my dealer.

11:04.130 --> 11:08.328
And these are my fans: Gunter, Kyoto
and Cecil Hampstead-on-Cecil-Cecil.

11:08.434 --> 11:11.062
So, uh, you guys are Eurotrash, huh?

11:11.170 --> 11:13.138
How's that working out for you?

11:13.239 --> 11:16.606
Eh, to be honest,
we are adrift in a sea...

11:16.709 --> 11:19.940
of decadent luxury
and meaningless sex.

11:20.046 --> 11:24.278
Uh-huh. So, uh, where might
this sea be located? Hmm?

11:24.383 --> 11:27.511
I must get back to my hotel and practice
my affectations for tomorrow.

11:27.620 --> 11:29.520
<i>Bonsoir.!
[ Pops ]</i>

11:29.622 --> 11:32.090
- What do we owe you, Moe?
- Nothing, nothing.

11:32.191 --> 11:35.627
Just give me a priceless sketch
with a certificate of authenticity.

11:35.728 --> 11:38.094
All right.
[ Muttering ]

11:38.197 --> 11:40.688
Hey, Moe!
Can I pay with a drawing?

11:40.800 --> 11:43.997
- Yeah. Nice try there, twelve step.
- [ Groans ]

11:46.072 --> 11:47.596
<i>[ Bird Squawks ]</i>

11:47.707 --> 11:52.144
Uh, Homer, you're making us
a little bit uncomfortable.

11:52.244 --> 11:55.873
Relax, big guy. He's just doing this for his art.
Right, Homer?

11:55.981 --> 11:59.151
Oh, yeah, art.

12:05.758 --> 12:07.749
<i>Here he is.
This is where the magic happens.</i>

12:07.860 --> 12:10.420
- Wonderful news, Homer.
- Is it about pies?

12:10.529 --> 12:12.429
I, um- No.

12:12.531 --> 12:16.729
We're going to hold a show
devoted entirely to you.

12:16.836 --> 12:21.739
Wow! It's like
Marge's dream come true- for me!

12:21.841 --> 12:24.571
Isn't that great, Marge?
For me.

12:24.677 --> 12:26.042
[ Groans ]

12:27.480 --> 12:29.380
Look, Marge.

12:29.482 --> 12:31.609
<i>They're advertising
my show in Art in America.</i>

12:31.717 --> 12:34.652
It's the first time I've been mentioned there-
that I know of.

12:34.754 --> 12:37.279
- I'm happy for you. Now good night.
- Good night.

12:38.390 --> 12:40.381
You're upset about something.

12:40.493 --> 12:43.621
Is this about that trip
Barney and I took to Machu Picchu?

12:43.729 --> 12:46.596
Oh, Homer,
being an artist was my dream.

12:46.699 --> 12:49.031
But now, without even trying...

12:49.135 --> 12:52.571
you've accomplished more in a week
than I have in my whole life.

12:52.671 --> 12:55.071
Aw, honey.
I've always liked your art.

12:55.174 --> 12:58.439
Your paintings look like
the things they look like.

12:58.544 --> 13:01.638
That's sweet.
But how would you like it if I-

13:01.747 --> 13:05.114
I don't know-
entered a belching contest.

13:05.217 --> 13:07.014
Frankly, I'd be a little turned on.

13:07.119 --> 13:09.644
[ Groans ]
You don't understand.

13:09.755 --> 13:12.883
Marge, I've screwed up
everything I've ever done.

13:12.992 --> 13:15.017
I mean, look at Bart.

13:15.127 --> 13:19.496
But I finally found something
where people worship me for screwing up.

13:19.598 --> 13:21.566
And that feels pretty good.

13:21.667 --> 13:25.228
<i>Well, I guess nothing else matters
as long as you're happy.</i>

13:25.337 --> 13:28.204
Now you're making sense.
Good night.

13:28.307 --> 13:30.275
<i>[ Snoring ]</i>

13:40.152 --> 13:42.279
Then I bought a Rembrandt-

13:42.388 --> 13:44.754
[ Burps ]

13:44.857 --> 13:46.518
Homer is the most dangerous artist
on the Springfield scene.

13:53.399 --> 13:55.492
<i>[ Applause ]</i>

13:55.601 --> 13:58.729
<i>I give you Botched Hibachi. The tricycle's
on loan from the Maggie Simpson collection.</i>

13:58.838 --> 14:00.806
This piece I call...

14:00.906 --> 14:04.774
<i>Failed Shelving Unit with
Stupid Stuck Chain Saw and Applesauce.</i>

14:04.877 --> 14:08.040
And finally,
my thing de resistance...

14:08.147 --> 14:11.275
<i>Attempted Birdhouse I.</i>

14:11.383 --> 14:13.851
[ Squawking ]

14:13.953 --> 14:15.978
[ All Murmuring ]

14:16.088 --> 14:19.353
Shall we start the bidding
at, say, $1 0,000?

14:19.458 --> 14:21.892
[ Throats Clearing ]

14:21.994 --> 14:24.462
All right.
How about a million?

14:24.563 --> 14:27.532
I'll give you two bucks for
the bird if it's still alive.

14:28.901 --> 14:32.598
What's going on here?
You weirdos love this stuff.

14:32.705 --> 14:35.833
Homer, I'm afraid they only love
what's new and shocking.

14:35.941 --> 14:38.501
These pieces are just like
your earlier work.

14:38.611 --> 14:41.205
You've gone from hip to boring.

14:41.313 --> 14:45.511
Why don't you call us
when you get to kitsch? [ Chuckles ]

14:45.618 --> 14:47.518
Come on, Gunter, Kyoto.

14:47.620 --> 14:50.316
- If we hurry, we can still catch the heroin craze.
- Mmm!

14:50.422 --> 14:52.856
Wait! Come back!
I'm a god to you!

14:52.958 --> 14:56.121
Worship me or fear my wrath!

14:56.228 --> 15:00.927
Oh, please, fear my wrath!
Please!

15:01.033 --> 15:03.058
Call me.

15:05.938 --> 15:09.931
I don't get it.
Why don't people like my art anymore?

15:10.042 --> 15:15.742
<i>Homer, I know you worked hard.
But all of your things were kind of the same.</i>

15:15.848 --> 15:20.547
Hey, RayJ.Johnson never changed his act,
and he's more popular now than he's ever been.

15:20.653 --> 15:22.746
- Who?
- You can call him Ray.

15:22.855 --> 15:26.552
Or you can call him J.
Or you can call him RayJ.

15:26.659 --> 15:29.753
- But you doesn't have to call him-
- I'm sick of him already.

15:29.862 --> 15:33.298
The point is, great artists
are always trying new things...

15:33.399 --> 15:36.197
like Michelangelo
or Shaquille O'Neal.

15:36.302 --> 15:38.827
You just need some inspiration.

15:40.472 --> 15:43.669
It's so exciting to do
something cultural together.

15:43.776 --> 15:49.009
Matt Groening? What's he doing in a museum?
He can barely draw!

15:49.114 --> 15:52.174
Ow! Oh, no!
I'm being erased!

15:52.284 --> 15:56.015
<i>Move it, bub.!
We got an installation to ''installate. ''</i>

15:56.121 --> 15:59.249
Ooh!
A Claes Oldenburg.

15:59.358 --> 16:01.849
<i>He's a European
who defied convention...</i>

16:01.961 --> 16:05.556
- and embraced American popular culture.
- [ Impressed Whistle ]

16:05.664 --> 16:08.326
He must be a hundred feet tall.

16:09.668 --> 16:12.068
Now this is a Joseph Turner.

16:12.171 --> 16:14.696
In an era when everyone else
painted portraits...

16:14.807 --> 16:17.970
he broke away by painting
the Venetian canals.

16:18.077 --> 16:21.410
It's glorious!
The streets are paved with water!

16:21.513 --> 16:23.447
You could ride a walrus to work!

16:23.549 --> 16:28.509
And Picasso started out painting realistically,
then moved on to cubism.

16:28.620 --> 16:32.420
By the end of his life,
he was just painting crank letters to the editor.

16:32.524 --> 16:34.719
<i>They call it his AngryJerk Period.</i>

16:34.827 --> 16:37.091
[ Guttural Sigh ]

16:37.196 --> 16:39.357
Mmm, split-pea.

16:39.465 --> 16:41.592
[ Gasps ]
With ham!

16:41.700 --> 16:45.500
- Any ideas yet?
- No. These guys are geniuses.

16:45.604 --> 16:48.903
I could never think of something
like soup or a pencil.

16:49.008 --> 16:50.532
Oh!

16:50.642 --> 16:53.475
I'm just gonna rest for a minute.

16:54.513 --> 16:56.413
[ Snoring ]

16:58.250 --> 17:00.150
[ Growling ]

17:01.186 --> 17:02.915
[ Sniffing ]

17:03.022 --> 17:06.082
- What the-Who the- Hey!
- [ Karate Yells ]

17:06.191 --> 17:08.159
[ Grunting, Groaning ]

17:09.828 --> 17:11.796
You're mean.

17:15.467 --> 17:17.935
<i>Hasta la vista, baby!</i>

17:18.971 --> 17:21.633
[ Groaning ]

17:21.740 --> 17:23.708
Hmm? Uhh!

17:23.809 --> 17:26.300
What the- Eww!

17:26.412 --> 17:28.107
[ Gasps ]
D'oh!

17:29.581 --> 17:32.311
<i>- [ Grunts ]
- Soup's on, fat boy.!</i>

17:32.418 --> 17:34.511
Ooh! Ow! Hey! No!

17:34.620 --> 17:37.282
No! Help! No! Ow!

17:37.389 --> 17:41.189
- No! Yo, Andy, no!
- Homer! Homer!

17:41.293 --> 17:45.821
Marge! Oh, why does art hate me?
I never did anything to art.

17:45.931 --> 17:47.899
Oh.
Let's get out of here.

17:49.635 --> 17:52.763
<i>Well, Dad, if the museum
didn't inspire you...</i>

17:52.871 --> 17:55.965
maybe you should do something
really radical, like Christo.

17:56.075 --> 17:58.600
Is he that jerk that revealed
the magicians' secrets?

17:58.710 --> 18:02.840
No, Christo is a conceptual artist
who does huge outdoor projects.

18:02.948 --> 18:05.348
He once wrapped the Reichstag
in plastic.

18:05.451 --> 18:08.318
- Not the Reichstag!
- Oh, yes.

18:08.420 --> 18:11.947
And he also set up hundreds of yellow umbrellas
along a California highway.

18:12.057 --> 18:15.754
- Why did he do that?
- To make the world a more magical place, I guess.

18:15.861 --> 18:18.295
Although they did blow over
and kill some people.

18:18.397 --> 18:21.264
Killer umbrellas?
Of course.

18:21.366 --> 18:23.266
Exquisite.

18:23.368 --> 18:26.997
No, Dad. No, my point is you have to do
something big and daring.

18:27.106 --> 18:29.301
Big? Daring?
Lisa, that's it!

18:29.408 --> 18:33.936
I've got an idea for a wonderful art project
that'll make everyone love me again!

18:34.046 --> 18:37.379
Step one:
steal all the doormats in town.

18:38.484 --> 18:40.748
Hit the road, ''Welcome Home''!

18:40.853 --> 18:43.549
Adios, ''Casa de Flanders''!

18:43.655 --> 18:46.522
See ya in hell,
''God Bless This House.''

18:46.625 --> 18:48.718
So long, ''The Simpsons''!

18:48.827 --> 18:50.852
<i>D'oh.!</i>

18:50.963 --> 18:54.364
<i>Step two:snorkel the animals.</i>

18:58.203 --> 19:01.900
<i>[ Panting ]
It wasn't easy, but I got all the grizzlies.</i>

19:02.007 --> 19:04.567
Great. I'll do the pony
while you do the lions.

19:04.676 --> 19:06.644
<i>Make sure you strap 'em on
real tight.</i>

19:06.745 --> 19:08.713
<i>Now, step three.</i>

19:10.449 --> 19:13.475
Are you sure this is art-
[ Coughs ] and not vandalism?

19:13.585 --> 19:15.951
That's for the courts
to decide, Son.

19:17.356 --> 19:19.256
[ Birds Twittering ]

19:20.292 --> 19:22.556
[ Creaking ]

19:22.661 --> 19:25.027
<i>[ Homer On Bullhorn ]
Wake up.! Wake up, Springfield.!</i>

19:25.130 --> 19:27.997
<i>I've got a surprise for you.</i>

19:28.100 --> 19:30.364
Oh, Lord! What now?

19:30.469 --> 19:33.370
- [ Chittering ]
- Oh, that can't be good.

19:33.472 --> 19:37.101
People of Springfield,
behold my latest work!

19:37.209 --> 19:39.905
Homer, what have you done?

19:40.012 --> 19:43.413
<i>It's conceptual art-
The Grand Canals of Springfield.</i>

19:43.515 --> 19:45.608
Just like Venice,
without the black plague.

19:45.717 --> 19:49.084
- What do you think?
- I think some people are going to be upset.

19:49.188 --> 19:51.156
I love it, Homer!

19:51.256 --> 19:53.690
You've turned this town
into a work of art!

19:53.792 --> 19:58.388
I just wish JasperJohns
hadn't stolen my boat. Aah!

19:58.497 --> 20:00.465
<i>So long, suckers.!</i>

20:00.566 --> 20:04.525
Well, they're in the business.
Real people might not be so understanding.

20:04.636 --> 20:08.697
<i>What the flood?
Maude, it's a miracle.!</i>

20:08.807 --> 20:12.038
The Lord has drowned the wicked
and spared the righteous.

20:12.144 --> 20:14.669
[ Gasps ]
Isn't that Homer Simpson?

20:14.780 --> 20:19.046
[ Scoffs ] Looks like heaven's easier
to get into than Arizona State.

20:20.552 --> 20:24.010
Ohh! I hate these flood pants.

20:27.159 --> 20:29.127
Hey, they're working!

20:29.228 --> 20:32.254
My feet are soaked,
but my cuffs are bone-dry!

20:32.364 --> 20:35.265
Everything's comin' up Milhouse!

20:38.403 --> 20:40.371
<i>[ Men, Women ]
Ahh.!</i>

20:40.472 --> 20:46.308
<i>##[ Man Singing Love Song ]</i>

20:52.351 --> 20:54.945
Edna, I'm gonna pop you a question...

20:55.053 --> 20:58.284
and... I hope the answer is yes.

20:58.390 --> 21:00.654
Do you think mother
would like this hat pin?

21:00.759 --> 21:02.727
Oh. Yes.

21:02.828 --> 21:05.820
Oh, you've made me
the happiest man on Earth!

21:15.140 --> 21:17.335
Well, Homer, I have to admit...

21:17.442 --> 21:20.275
you created something
people really love.

21:20.379 --> 21:22.347
You truly are an artist.

21:22.447 --> 21:26.042
No. I'm just a nut
who couldn't build a barbecue.

21:26.151 --> 21:28.881
You'll always be the artist
in the family.

21:28.987 --> 21:31.114
- Aww.
- Is that our house?

21:31.223 --> 21:33.487
- Yep.
- And is that us on the roof?

21:33.592 --> 21:36.857
- That's us.
- Are we kissing?

21:36.962 --> 21:39.624
Oh, I don't know.
Could be.

21:39.731 --> 21:42.029
I need some inspiration.

21:44.136 --> 21:46.604
<i>##[ Man Singing Love Song
Continues ]</i>

21:51.276 --> 21:53.176
Yoink!

21:55.747 --> 21:58.011
<i>##[ Continues ]</i>

22:17.803 --> 22:19.828
<i>##[ Ends ]</i>

22:41.126 --> 22:43.094
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

